    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2021-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2021-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support public advocacy, awareness raising and sensitization on prevention and response via both new and traditional media platforms
Support informal workers to reinstitute their jobs/livelihood
Collaborate with informal sector to promote the manufacture, assembling, production and design of homegrown lifesaving solutions including disinfectants, sanitizers and masks for health care facilities in accordance with WHO guidelines
Support informal worker efforts in fighting COVID-19, protecting jobs and safeguarding SDG progress
Promote the aligning social protection to the 2030 Sustainable Development Agenda
Provide advice and technical assistance to support the Government to use social protection as a policy for sustainable development.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">To safeguard informal workers&#x2019; livelihoods from the disruptive effects of COVID-19: 30 women who rendered jobless due to the closure of business as a result of the COVID-19 were given with livelihood support of Nakfa 3,000.00 each; 3 youths in Asmara and 2 women in Keren town were rehabilitated through the provision of shoeshine stations; 3 vulnerable households in Keren and other 5 households in the Northern Red Sea Region have been given cash and in-kind assistance to establish small mercantile businesses and 50 women heads of household residing in and around Tokombia were given 10 female goats each to assist them rebuild back their livestock assets and livelihoods. The above supports and initiatives have enhanced the productive capacity of the households by diversifying and/or rebuilding back their productive base and assets</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
